    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think maybe the wording 'design _choice_' is better than 'design bug' :-) \nBecause, there is indeed something to say for the logic you lay out, but there are certainly also good reasons to choose the current behaviour. You want to return one group, but if there is nothing to group by, how can you have a group? Eg, how would you call this group? `None`? What would be the index of the resulting frame if you do eg `df.groupby(by=()).mean()`?\n"
  },
