    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "yeah, IIRC this is really to catch errors as there are multiple specifiers `by,axis,level`, so passing nothing is really a user error, where you want to fail fast.\n\nFurthermore @jorisvandenbossche point is that this would essentially give rise to a single NaN keyed group, which are currently excluded. I suppose if that were relaxed (a bit non-trivial actually, #443) then this might be realistic.\n"
